eathable additionally new jackets featured interchangeable shells and liners multiple wearing options and fabric technology fueled rapid sales growth columbia became a publicly traded company in  it acquired footwear maker sorel corporation in  and mountain hardwear in  in  columbia acquired the pacific trail and montrail brands columbia sportswears company headquarters in washington county oregon in  the company moved its headquarters from portland to a site in an unincorporated part of washington county in the cedar mill area and just outside the beaverton city limits the site on nw science park drive has a portland mailing address but is not in portland in  city of portland officials attempted to convince columbia sportswear to move back to portland but the company ultimately rejected the idea and said it would expand its existing headquarters instead on june   columbia sportswear announced a threeyear sponsorship of the cycling team formerly known as team high road and before that tmobile and team telekom the sponsorship began on july   with the start of the tour de france the teams name was team columbia the sponsorship included both the mens and womens teams on august   columbia sportswear company signed an agreement to acquire outdry technologies srl which owns the intellectual property and other assets comprising the outdry brand and related business via a cash purchase from nextec srl based near milan italy the transaction is expected to close during the third quarter of  subject to customary closing conditions and is not expected to have a material effect on the companys  operating results in march  bryan timm was named company president taking over that position from tim boyle who remains ceo logoedit the company logo has been noticed to resemble a swastika but the fact that the company was founded by german jews who fled nazi germany can be considered proof enough that the logo is not inspired by the nazi symbol locationsedit columbias flagship store in downtown portland oregon columbia sportswear distributes its products in more than  countries and  retailers columbia also operates its own chain of retail stores including its flagship store located in downtown portland oregon financial informationedit as of february   the companys market capitalization is about  billioncitation needed with  net sales of  billion stock exchangesedit columbia sportswear company is publicly traded on nasdaq with ticker symbol colm see alsoedit companies portal list of companies based in oregon list of outdoor industry parent companies referencesedit  columbia sportswear company  annual report  a b c d e brettman allan april   columbia charts its next billion dollars the oregonian p c retrieved    columbia sportswear company shareholder information retrieved    senior jeanie november   seamless warehouse is a marvel portland tribune archived from the original on june   retrieved    columbia milestones columbia sportswear retrieved    binole gina april   columbia goes public in topoftheline style portland business journal retrieved    columbia sportswear now owns pacific trail portland business journal march   retrieved    columbia sportswear buys montrail seattle postintelligencer january   retrieved    a b dworkin andy august   columbia sportswear staying put the oregonian retrieved    columbias tough mother squashes return rumor portland business journal march   retrieved    columbia sportswear announces sponsorship press release team columbia  high road sports inc june   archived from the original on  retrieved    columbia sportswear company to acquire outdry technologies srl press release business wire august   retrieved    fanshawe student union fanshawe logo launches with frosty reception external linksedit wikimedia commons has media related to columbia sportswear company official website v t e oregonbased companies nyse listed greenbrier companies lithia motors nike nw natural portland general electric nasdaq listed columbia s